{
  "texts": [
    "The open-access nature of Bloom, coupled with its linguistic diversity, provides a valuable resource for researchers working on global and cross-linguistic natural language processing tasks.",
    "VicunaVicuna [55] is an open-source, fine-tuned LLM derived from LLaMA and developed by a collaboration of researchers.",
    "It is designed to enhance the capabilities of existing models by leveraging supervised fine-tuning techniques.",
    "Vicuna is fine-tuned on a dataset that includes conversations, making it particularly adept at dialogue-based tasks.",
    "The model's architecture is based on the transformer framework, and it employs a causal language modeling objective similar to other large-scale language models."
  ]
}